26. How do you Import Modules?
You import a module in Python by using the import keyword followed by the name of the module.
example: import math
Why import modules?
To reuse already written code instead of rewriting functionality.

27. What are Built-in Modules?
Built-in modules are modules that come pre-installed with Python and provide ready-made functionality.
examples:
math-mathematical operation
random-The Python random module is a built-in library used to generate pseudo-random numbers and perform randomized operations like shuffling data or picking random items from a collection.
datetime - used to manipulate dates, times, and time intervals.
os -  provides a portable way to interact with the underlying operating system
sys - a built-in library that provides variables and functions used to interact directly with the Python interpreter and manage its runtime environment. 

28. What is the with Statement?
The with statement automatically manages resources and ensures they are properly closed after use.
if any error occurs the pyhton files remains open so using with statemrnt the file will be automatically closed

